  "level": 0,
  "ordinal": 0,
  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nChina's coal production averaged 367.1 million tons in January/February. This marks a decline of 35.6 million tons (-9%) from December's record production but is up year-on-year by 23.8 million tons (7%). As we have been stressing in our work, the government last year shifted its focus to ensuring robust coal production rather than focusing on mine safety.",
